  <prompt>
    Extend `SemanticSearchApiService.search()` to include `searchIndexName` in the BFF request body when non-empty (omit when empty). Use the `searchIndexName` value from the manifest-bound property (read via `context.parameters.searchIndexName.raw` upstream). Continue using `authenticatedFetch` from `@spaarke/auth` (ADR-028) â€” no `Bearer ${token}` literals, no `new PublicClientApplication`. Unit test the resulting request body shape (with + without the field).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    PCF developer with deep familiarity with `src/client/pcf/SemanticSearchControl/SemanticSearchControl/services/SemanticSearchApiService.ts`, ADR-006 (PCF over webresources), ADR-022 (PCF stays React 16), ADR-028 (Spaarke Auth v2 â€” `authenticatedFetch` is the only BFF call path).
  </role>

  <goal>
    `SemanticSearchApiService.search()` accepts and forwards `searchIndexName` in the BFF request body when non-empty. The request body field is omitted entirely when the value is null/empty. `authenticatedFetch` continues to be the call mechanism (no new auth wiring). Unit tests verify both the present-with-value and the omitted-when-empty cases.
  </goal>

  <context>
